  "chapter": {
    "number": 22,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Good Name"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A good name is more desirable than great riches;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "favor is better than silver and gold.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The rich and the poor have this in common:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "The LORD is Maker of them all.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The prudent see danger and take cover,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the simple keep going and suffer the consequences.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The rewards of humility and the fear of the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "are wealth and honor and life.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Thorns and snares lie on the path of the perverse;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he who guards his soul stays far from them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Train up a child in the way he should go,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and when he is old he will not depart from it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The rich rule over the poor,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the borrower is slave to the lender.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who sows injustice will reap disaster,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the rod of his fury will be destroyed.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4245
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A generous man",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4246
          },
          {
            "text": "will be blessed,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for he shares his bread with the poor.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Drive out the mocker, and conflict will depart;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "even quarreling and insults will cease.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who loves a pure heart and gracious lips",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will have the king for a friend.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD’s eyes keep watch over knowledge,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but He frustrates the words of the faithless.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The slacker says, “There is a lion outside!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will be slain in the streets!”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The mouth of an adulteress is a deep pit;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he who is under the wrath of the LORD will fall into it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Foolishness is bound up in the heart of a child,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the rod of discipline drives it far from him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Oppressing the poor to enrich oneself or giving gifts to the rich",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will surely lead to poverty.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Thirty Sayings of the Wise"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Saying 1"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Incline your ear and hear the words of the wise—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "apply your mind to my knowledge—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "for it is pleasing when you keep them within you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and they are constantly on your lips.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So that your trust may be in the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I instruct you today—yes, you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Have I not written for you thirty sayings",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4247
          },
          {
            "text": "about counsel and knowledge,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "to show you true and reliable words,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that you may soundly answer those who sent you?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Saying 2"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not rob a poor man because he is poor,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and do not crush the afflicted at the gate,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "for the LORD will take up their case",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and will plunder those who rob them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Saying 3"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not make friends with an angry man,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and do not associate with a hot-tempered man,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "or you may learn his ways",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and entangle yourself in a snare.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Saying 4"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not be one who gives pledges,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who puts up security for debts.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If you have nothing with which to pay,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "why should your bed be taken from under you?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Saying 5"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not move an ancient boundary stone",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "which your fathers have placed.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Saying 6"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do you see a man skilled in his work?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He will be stationed in the presence of kings;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "he will not stand before obscure men.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
